				GlipSOE - Hey there Xyrrus! Well, for starters most folks can actually physically play the game on their machines now. That wasn&#8217;t always the case, as I&#8217;m sure you well know. Aside of that we finally got in a lot of the things we wanted to have in originally (flying mounts is a great example of that, APW is another).<br />
GlipSOE - I also think we&#8217;ve done a pretty good job at getting rid of a lot of the barriers to entry that kept folks out to begin with. Steep learning curves on certain things, system that&#8217;s weren&#8217;t explained enough, etc. With the Isle of Dawn coming soon that will be improved even more as well.<br />
GlipSOE - All in all the game is just a lot more polished and a lot more fun. All those little changes and fixes over the course of a year really add up in a big way when you sit back and look at them as a whole.<br />
GlipSOE - Is it the game I had hoped it'd be? Well, gnomes haven't overtaken Telon yet so we've got a little ways to go still *grin* -- but its definitely getting there! <br />
<br />
TirasleeSOE - We have a coder dedicated to improving our tools every day, and yes, they are much faster than they used to be. We learned a lot about our tools during the development of APW. There is still room for improvement and we are constantly working to eliminate the existing problems so we can deliver content faster without sacrificing quality. 
			
