							What I understood as message is:<br />
<br />
<ul><li style="">We will change old things to make them look different instead of creating something new. Examples are Pantheon, zone reshaping and the character models.</li><li style="">We still have dreams but lacking the resources to realize them. Examples are the talk about an expansion, Galleons and talking about high level content in contrast to what I’ve see happening in the last few months in game.</li><li style="">We change things without fully understanding what the impact is. Examples are the back and forth with BoP, some of the class balances and the reintroduction of lag with every GU.</li></ul><br />
<br />
I understand, with the racial mounts was new content introduced with GU5 but this content is so totally off from what I’m looking for. I’m as well ok that the dev teams focuses at the moment on Isle of Dawn because the trail may bring benefit to the game. But I’m pretty sure it will not bring benefit for me.<br />
<br />
I don’t understand the message when someone is saying people come back to the game. I have seen several guilds dying in the last few weeks, because almost everybody is gone. Sure, 2 or 3 of the people checking out AoC are showing up again because it is worse for them than Vanguard. But these people get as welcome present lag in APW which makes raids almost unplayable. How long do you think they will stay?<br />
<br />
My message may be received very negative but I’m talking with people who have left the game month ago and if they ask me why I still play Vanguard it is very difficult to answer for me. Except maybe that I can say I did not find something interesting to play somewhere else until now and I like the people I’m with.
